Original Java code:

if the input is 1. Then, input x=1 is odd. So the code doesn't do x++. Then, enters the next loop (the infinite while loop):

Inside, compute sqrt(1)=1 → loop over i from 3 to 1, which doesn't run. the i variable would be set to 3 (since initial i is 3 and not exceeds sqrt(1)=1) → then after loop, i is 3, sqrt(1) is 1. So checking i > sqrtNum → 3>1 → yes, break the outer loop. So outputs 1, which is not a prime. So the original Java code has a bug.

After that, the code has if (i > sqrtNum) break (to exit the outer loop? Wait no, the outer loop is a while (true). Wait the code after for loop:

if (i > sqrtNum) break; 
then the outer loop breaks, so x is considered as prime.
